{
  "name": "2 · Sync to SharePoint",
  "version": "2.0.0",
  "description": "Two-phase wiki-to-SharePoint sync: convert md→docx locally, then upload via SharePoint MCP to OneDrive > Artifacts/wiki-sync/",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },


### preamble — Details
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the SharePoint sync pipeline end-to-end:\n\n1. Phase 1 — Stage .docx files: Run `python3 ~/shared/tools/sharepoint-sync/cli.py --mode directory --output-path ~/shared/tools/sharepoint-sync/output` and show the sync report summary (created/updated/skipped/failed counts).\n\n2. If Phase 1 produced any created or updated files, proceed to Phase 2 — Upload to SharePoint: Run `python3 ~/shared/tools/sharepoint-sync/sp-upload.py` to get the upload plan JSON. For each entry in the plan, call sharepoint_write_file with libraryName='Documents', folderPath=entry.sp_folder, fileName=entry.filename, sourcePath=entry.local_path. Upload in parallel batches of 10 for speed.\n\n3. Show final results: how many files uploaded, any failures, and the SharePoint target path.\n\nIf Phase 1 shows 0 created and 0 updated, skip Phase 2 and report 'No changes to sync.'"
  }
}